My Production Suggestion
For your kind of infrastructure (data center / server-focused):
Primary: Raw LVM volumes or direct SAN/FC LUNs
Secondary: LVM-thin if storage efficiency matters
Avoid: qcow2 for critical production VMs unless snapshots are a major requirement

Example:
virt-install --disk path=/dev/vg_kvm/vm01_disk,format=raw

Bottom Line
Raw + LVM/direct block storage is the industry-preferred production standard for KVM due to performance, simplicity, and reliability.
